TITLE: Snap plunges more than 25% on third-quarter revenue miss
SUMMARY: Snap reported disappointing revenue figures on Thursday, after the company put in place cost-cutting measures to boost profit.

TITLE: American Airlines expects fourth-quarter profit thanks to strong travel demand
SUMMARY: American's revenue rose to a record $13.46 billion in the three months ended Sept. 30, up 13% from 2019 despite flying nearly 10% less.

TITLE: Elon Musk addresses Twitter takeover, possible recession on Tesla earnings call
SUMMARY: Tesla's net income (GAAP) for Q3 2022 reached $3.33 billion and automotive margins remained stable at 27.9%.

TITLE: IBM surpasses quarterly projections and lifts its full-year revenue forecast
SUMMARY: IBM saw a jump in mainframe computer and transaction-processing software sales in its first full quarter of sales of a new version, the z16, in May.

TITLE: Procter & Gamble's earnings beat as higher pricing offsets drop in volume
SUMMARY: Shares of Procter & Gamble have fallen 21% this year, dragging its market value down to $306.4 billion.

TITLE: Globally critical chip firm ASML jumps 6% after earnings; sees limited impact from U.S. China curbs
SUMMARY: ASML reported third-quarter earnings that topped analyst expectations, bucking the trend of a slowdown seen by other semiconductor companies.

TITLE: Netflix adds more than 2.4 million subscribers, reveals details about password-sharing crackdown
SUMMARY: Netflix reported third-quarter earnings after the bell. Here are the results.

TITLE: Adobe stock jumps on estimates for next year as strong dollar cuts into growth
SUMMARY: Adobe CEO Shantanu Narayen says the company's success continues, but it's not immune from fluctuation in currencies.

TITLE: United shrugs off recession fears as workers 'untethered from the desk' fuel travel demand
SUMMARY: United said it expects another profit for the fourth quarter.

TITLE: Hasbro profit misses the mark as toy maker faces high inventory and inflation
SUMMARY: Hasbro reported Q3 earnings that missed expectations and revenue that matched Wall Street projections.

TITLE: Goldman shares jump after topping analysts' expectations on strong bond trading results
SUMMARY: Goldman's traders tend to outperform other banks during periods of high volatility, which helped the firm in the third quarter.

TITLE: Bank of America tops estimates on better-than-expected bond trading, higher interest rates
SUMMARY: Bank of America said U.S. consumers have "remained resilient with strong, although slower growing, spending levels" and elevated deposits.

TITLE: Citigroup reports 25% decline in third-quarter profits but tops revenue expectations
SUMMARY: CEO Jane Fraser is trying to turn around the massive bank during a volatile period for markets and the global economy.

TITLE: Wells Fargo shares jump 3% as bank tops expectations despite boosting loan loss reserves
SUMMARY: Wells Fargo on Friday reported lower quarterly earnings than a year ago as a decision to build up reserves cut into profit.

TITLE: Morgan Stanley shares drop 4% after missing profit estimate as investment banking revenue collapses
SUMMARY: Wall Street banks are grappling with the collapse in IPOs and issuance this year, a sharp reversal from the deals boom that drove results last year.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase tops estimates as bank reaps more interest income than expected after jump in rates
SUMMARY: JPMorgan Chase on Friday posted results that topped analysts' estimates as the biggest U.S. bank by assets took advantage of rising rates.

TITLE: Domino's reports U.S. same-store sales increase and stands by forecast for food costs
SUMMARY: Domino's Pizza reported an increase in U.S. same-store sales and stood by its forecast for food costs this year.

TITLE: Walgreens beats sales expectations, as it expands its health-care business
SUMMARY: Walgreens' profit outlook for the new fiscal year is largely in line with Wall Street's expectations.

TITLE: Delta forecasts another profit after summer boom drives record revenue
SUMMARY: Delta forecast another profit and revenue above 2019 levels for the last three months of the year.

TITLE: PepsiCo hikes forecast after higher pricing helps boost revenue
SUMMARY: PepsiCo reported earnings Wednesday morning that beat analyst expectations.

TITLE: Nike shares fall as overstocked inventory weighs on earnings
SUMMARY: Nike said its revenue rose in its fiscal first-quarter despite supply-chain volatility, while swollen inventories weighed on its profit.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond reports 28% drop in sales as it presses ahead with turnaround plan
SUMMARY: Bed Bath & Beyond's results didn't reflect the struggling, debt-laden retailer's turnaround plan, which it announced in August.

TITLE: Lego sales jump 17% in first half of 2022, boosted by Star Wars and Harry Potter sets
SUMMARY: Lego revenue jumped 17% during the first six months of 2022, boosted by top-selling building set tie-ins with Star Wars and Harry Potter.

TITLE: FedEx hikes package rates, details cost cutting as demand weakens globally
SUMMARY: FedEx announced rate hikes and detailed its cost-cutting efforts after warning last week it was seeing demand weaken globally.

TITLE: Olive Garden sales fall short, but parent company Darden stands by outlook
SUMMARY: Darden Restaurants reported mixed quarterly results but still reiterated its outlook for fiscal 2023.

TITLE: FedEx shares sink after company cites weakening global demand
SUMMARY: Shares of FedEx sank Friday morning after the company withdrew its full-year guidance and cited weakening global demand.

TITLE: Oracle reports 18% revenue growth after Cerner deal closes
SUMMARY: Oracle said electronic health-record software maker Cerner contributed $1.4 billion to quarterly revenue.

TITLE: GameStop reports wider loss, announces partnership with crypto exchange FTX
SUMMARY: GameStop said quarterly sales declined and losses widened, as its inventory of video game equipment and more swelled.

TITLE: Nio reports wider second-quarter loss despite increase in EV shipments
SUMMARY: Nio's second-quarter loss widened, but the company expects higher production and deliveries in the third quarter.

TITLE: Lululemon jumps after it boosts outlook and posts strong earnings beat
SUMMARY: Lululemon reported second quarter earnings after the bell on Thursday.
